headline: Kroger Taps Greg Foran As CEO To Sharpen Execution And E Commerce
summary: Kroger (NYSE:KR) has appointed Greg Foran as its new CEO and board member. Foran, former CEO of Walmart U.S. and Air New Zealand, will succeed interim CEO Ron Sargent. The appointment follows an extended interim period and a global search for new leadership. Kroger is one of the largest grocery retailers in the U.S., operating supermarkets, pharmacies, and digital grocery platforms. The move to bring in Greg Foran comes as the grocery sector faces intense competition from big box retailers,...
